Background: Winkler Land Company is proposing to build a 351 lot single
family home subdivision, generally located north of County Road 50 and
west of Cedar Avenue in Lakeville, MN. The subdivision will be built in
phases with the entire development anticipated to be completed by 2034.
This study analyzed the potential traffic impacts of the built out subdivision
on key intersections within and near the subdivision.
Results: The traffic impacts of the proposed subdivision on the study
intersections were analyzed in the 2034 build-out conditions. The
i. The forecast traffic from the proposed development will have little
impact on the operations of the study intersections.
ii. All study intersections will operate acceptably through the 2034 build-

iii. The County Road 50/Holyoke Avenue and County Road 50/Cedar
Avenue intersections currently meet peak hour warrants for a traffic
signal and are forecast to experience LOS F operations in the 2034
scenarios if no mitigations are made. Installing traffic signals at these
intersections would provide acceptable operations through the 2034

existing traffic would not cause unacceptable traffic operations,

Recommendations: Other than constructing the roadways per the
subdivision site plan, no modifications are needed to be made by the
developer to the study intersections (such as adding turn lanes or
installing traffic signals). It is recommended the east/west approaches to
stop sign controlled while the north/south approaches are uncontrolled
after the intersections are constructed. Dakota County should monitor the
County Road 50/Holyoke Avenue and County Road 50/Cedar Avenue
intersections for possible future upgrade to traffic signal control.

Traffic forecasts were developed for the year 2034 No-Build Scenario
based on several different growth rates. The Dakota County 2030
Transportation Plan forecasts traffic volumes along County Road 50 near
the site to grow at a 3.9% compounded annual growth rate. This equates
to an increase of 116% from 2014 volumes to 2034 volumes. This growth
rate was applied to movements on County Road 50.
The Dakota County 2030 Transportation Plan forecasts volumes along
Cedar Avenue near the site to grow at a 1.9% compounded annual growth
rate. This equates to an increase of 45% from 2014 volumes to 2034
volumes. This growth rate was applied to movements on Cedar Avenue.
In 2011, Mn/DOT assigned a 20 year growth rate of 1.6, or a 60%
increase. This growth rate was applied to movements at all other
locations in the study network with the exception of the Highview
Growth from these two intersections is likely to all be due to traffic
generated by the site, so no background growth was applied at these
Traffic forecasts were developed for the year 2034 Build Scenarios by
adding the traffic generated by the proposed development to the 2034 No-
Build volumes. The resultant 2034 Build peak hour forecasts are shown in
the Appendix under the capacity analysis section for each scenario.
